This README contains instructions for running the version of pokete
we have been working on over the last few weeks. It is important that
you do not follow the install instructions in the original README, as
our changes have not all been pushed upstream.

To install pokete with the changes we have made, do the following:
    - Clone this repo https://github.com/squidaboni/COMP490_Final.git
    - In a terminal, navigate to the project folder and run 'pip install -e'.
    - To confirm you are running the forked version, run the command 'pip show pokete'.
      If the 'Editable project location:' is a folder on your personal device, and does
      not include 'site packages', then you are all set.
    - To play the game, in your terminal run the command 'python -m pokete'.
    - ...
